Removing units from Mileage, Engine and Max_Power columns¶

df["Engine"] =  df["Engine"].str.extract('(\d+)').astype(float)
df["Max_Power"] =  df["Max_Power"].str.extract('(\d+)').astype(float)

In [10]:
from sklearn import preprocessing
categorical_columns = x[['Fuel', 'Seller_Type','Transmission', 'Owner']].copy()
ohe_cols= pd.get_dummies(categorical_columns)
x = pd.concat([x,ohe_cols], axis=1)
x.drop(columns=['Fuel', 'Seller_Type','Transmission', 'Owner'],inplace=True)

In [46]:
random_parameters = {'n_estimators': [4, 8, 16, 32],                # Number of trees in random forest
                     'max_features': ['auto', 'sqrt'],              # Number of features to consider at every split
                     'max_depth': [4, 8, 12, 16],                   # Maximum number of levels in tree
                     'min_samples_split': [4, 8, 16, 32],           # Minimum number of samples required to split a node
                     'min_samples_leaf': [4, 8],                    # Minimum number of samples required at each leaf node
                     'bootstrap': [True, False]}                    # Method of selecting samples for training each tree

               'min_samples_split': [*range(12,20)], # Minimum number of samples required to split a node
